HEADWORD: Polyphase
<hw>Pol"y*phase</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets>
+ <ets>phase</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>Having or producing
two or more phases; multiphase; <as>as, a <ex>polyphase</ex> machine, a
machine producing two or more pressure waves of electro-motive force,
differing in phase; a <ex>polyphase</ex> current</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

